cafes.name: The Cafe Meow
cafes.address: 3524 Winnetka Ave N, New Hope, MN 55427, USA

text.text:
My daughter and I went here for her 7th birthday. It was a great experience! The employees were so friendly and kind, the coffee was so good, and we even bought some collars for our cats and macarons which were so yummy!
The Cafe is for anyone but to visit the cats you must be 7+ and it's an additional cost. I recommend scheduling an appointment online in advance, especially on the weekends. It was definitely worth every cent to play with the cats and see how excited and happy my daughter was!
The staff is extremely friendly and helpful. I enjoyed talking with them. The have cute items to purchase. I enjoyed the coffee drink I got and my boyfriend loved his hot chocolate.

Loved the atmosphere, you can sip on coffee, kit-TEA, espurresso, soda, or nibble on a muffin or cookie while watching a bunch of cats play in a segregated room with a see through plastic/glass wall. That way, you don't have to worry about any animals getting into your food or spilling your drink and still be able to watch a bunch of cats play. They also have cute  names for the drinks such as kit-TEA (kitty) for instance, or esPURResso (espresso) with little cat puns in them. Or, Ex-purr-esso instead of expresso.  Cat-finated instead of caffeinated is another good pun that they had as well.  There are also gifts you can buy like cat merchandise such as a bag with cats on it, cat nip, etc. If you do go inside to see the cats, there's hand sanitizer to use before going inside and then after when you come out of the cat room. Cat play toys are inside the room, so you can play with the cats. There are chairs and tables for you to sit on (this way, kitties will jump onto your lap since they ask that you don't pick up cats). Cats are well socialized, so a number of them will actually walk up to you to be petted. Additionally, They have little biographies with the name of each cat and a photo describing what each kitty is like (for example, they might mention in the bio that a cat is "shy at first but will be a love bug once getting to know you", or "loves human food", or "friendly with dogs and kids"). My experience there was the cat's meow (bad pun, i know but twas really a dandy time.)

cafes.name: The Cafe Meow
cafes.address: 1718A Lexington Ave N, Roseville, MN 55113, USA

text.text: I had such a great time at this place! There are games, books, fun products to buy (I left with multiple things), GREAT coffee, and cute cats. The staff is wonderful. I highly recommend this place! You DO need to make a reservation online if you’d like to visit the area with the cats. It is so worth it!

I love to grab a coffee and play with kittens for an hour to forget that we still have 9 more months of winter. Just make sure you get a reservation because they’re popular! The kitties are well cared for by a staff who do a great job at keeping everyone safe and happy.
Super friendly staff and they really care about the cats here. I loved my time interacting with the cats. They were all so cute and playful at 11am.

cafes.name: Wired Whisker
cafes.address: 1823 E Superior St, Duluth, MN 55812, USA

text.text: I went there for the grand opening, and i absolutely love it. The baked goods and coffee are wonderful and being able to socialize with the cats makes this a purrfect destination for locals and tourists alike. Bear in mind that you do have to book a reservation to access the cat lounge, but it's super easy to do and very affordable on their website. Their cat roster does also change periodically since they work with animal rescues, and you may very well meet your new fuzzy best friend here.

Such an amazing place!! I actually didn't order any food or drink, but I did go into the kitty area! Ton of the cats were really interactive and wanted to sit on my lap. If you're looking to adopt, would highly recommend going here!! Kitties looked all so well taken care of!!

I cannot say anything about the adoption process, but visiting the cats on my birthday was a treat! I had a tea and a delicious cat-themed macaron. I was able to walk in, as no one had booked online, but had to wait about 15 minutes for the next hour to rollover (which I fully expected). The cats were mostly napping, but there was one who played a bit and then sat in my lap.

Saint Paul.name: Catzen Coffee
Saint Paul.address: 1416 Grand Ave, St Paul, MN 55105, USA

text.text: So excited to have a new cat cafe in the twin cities! I made a reservation for the living room where the cats are, which was such a cute space. Keep in mind that the cats are able to come and go from the living room as they please, so you probably will not see them all. However I really liked that set up because I'm sure the cats are much more comfortable that way. I also liked that buying a drink counts as admission. Overall a great community space to drink some coffee, play some games, and see some cats!

The staff were very welcoming, I got the chocolate chip banana bread and vanilla latte . It was delicious the best latte I’ve had in awhile had a very rich flavoring to it. When I walked in someone at the door immediately greeted me and asked for my name to add me to the wait list to visit with the cats. I got there at about 10:20 and was able to go in the cat room at 10:45. Gave me just the right amount of time to enjoy my latte and banana bread. Got to stay in the cat den until 11:30, I feel 45 minutes was the perfect amount of time. I like that they use this system this was the cat den was not to full and crowded. The cats were so sweet and when I used the bathroom I noticed they had pads and tampons In the bathroom for no charge I thought that was really nice! Definitely will be coming back.

Absolutely LOVE this place and wish I could give it more stars! We came at a busy time but everyone was friendly, service was fast, coffee & food was delicious and we were in to see the cats in only a few minutes.

The negative reviews are clearly from folks with an ax to grind, I wouldn’t pay any attention to them. Rules regarding children are for the cats safety and for everyone’s enjoyment. I’m all for their rules and it’s one of the main reasons I will continue to go back!

I highly recommend checking Catzen Coffee out! You won’t be disappointed!
